Package org.example.galaxy_trucker.Commands

package org.example.galaxy_trucker.Commands
  • Class
    Description
    AcceptCommand
    The AcceptCommand class is a specific implementation of the Command class that handles acceptance-related logic during game execution.
    AddCrewCommand
    Represents a command to add crew members to a player's game board.
    BuildingCommand
    BuildingCommand represents a specific type of command that is used for managing and executing actions related to building operations in the game.
    ChoosingPlanetsCommand
    Represents a command that allows a player to choose a planet during gameplay.
    Command
    Represents a base abstract class for all game commands, providing a framework for various command types within the game system.
    CommandInterpreter
    The CommandInterpreter class is responsible for parsing and interpreting command strings, converting them into appropriate Command objects for execution.
    CommandInterpreter.CommandCreator
     
    ConsumeEnergyCommand
    Represents a command to consume energy within the context of the game.
    DebugShip
    The DebugShip class represents a specialized command in the game to debug and modify the player's ship setup.
    DefendFromLargeCommand
    Represents the DefendFromLargeCommand, a specific type of command that allows players to defend against large scale threats in the game.
    DefendFromSmallCommand
    Represents a command to defend a player from small-scale threats in the game.
    FinishBuildingCommand
    The FinishBuildingCommand class represents a specific type of game command that allows a player to finalize the construction of a building.
    GiveAttackCommand
    Represents a specific command in the game, used to perform an attack action with optional coordinates.
    GiveSpeedCommand
    Represents a command that grants engine power to components on a player's game board.
    HandleCargoCommand
    The HandleCargoCommand class represents a command in the game responsible for handling various cargo-related actions.
    KillCommand
    The KillCommand class represents a game command that targets and eliminates specific game elements located at certain coordinates.
    LobbyCommand
    Represents a command used within the lobby system of the game.
    LoginCommand
    LoginCommand is a specific implementation of the abstract Command class, representing the action of logging into a game.
    QuitCommand
    Represents a command used to handle player quit functionality within the game.
    ReadyCommand
    Represents the ReadyCommand used to handle player readiness in the game system.
    ReconnectCommand
    Represents a command used to facilitate reconnection of a player to a game session.
    RemoveTileCommand
    Represents a command to remove a tile from the player board.
    SelectChunkCommand
    Represents a command to select a specific chunk in a game.
    Theft
    Represents the Theft command in the game, allowing a player to steal or lose cargo based on the provided details.
    TheftCommand
    Represents a command for stealing cargo from a specific position and coordinate within a game.
